


**************HARDWARE SHOPPING LIST ESSENTIALS**************

• Raspberry Pi (I used a model B as the ethernet port is useful for setup)
• SD card with palladium installed
• Photo cell (CdS photoresistor)
• 5 W laser 
• A button
• Some wire or connectors
• Some type of case
• A mirror

**************HARDWARE SHOPPING LIST OPTIONAL**************
• Wifi dongle (The one that ships with the Ninja Blocks works, or skip if you want a wired device)
• Laser mount
• A mini amp with speaker (or just plug headphones in)
• Fibre optic Light Transporter http://www.jaycar.com.au/productView.asp?ID=HP1193
• Adafruit Pi Cobbler Kit http://learn.adafruit.com/adafruit-pi-cobbler-kit
• Half-size breadboard http://www.adafruit.com/products/64

**************BUILD HARDWARE**************

Attach Pi Cobbler to Pi
http://learn.adafruit.com

Set up LDR to breadboard
http://learn.adafruit.com/basic-resistor-sensor-reading-on-raspberry-pi/basic-photocell-reading

Set up button to breadboard
http://learn.adafruit.com/playing-sounds-and-using-buttons-with-raspberry-pi/

Connect laser to breadboard
http://learn.adafruit.com/basic-resistor-sensor-reading-on-raspberry-pi/basic-photocell-reading
